        <![CDATA[
        Allow calls from numbers that share a prefix with your existing contacts,
        ideal for organizations using sequential phone lines (e.g., clinics or offices). <br>
        <br>
        <b>Options</b>: <br>
        <minor>Suffix Variation Length</minor><br>
        &ensp; Ignore last N digits. <br>
        <br>
        <b>For example:</b> <br>
        <sample>
        &ensp; With xxxx02 in your contacts and a suffix tolerance of 2, any number from xxxx00 to xxxx99 will be allowed.
        </sample>
        ]]>
